1
00:00:15,370 --> 00:00:16,770
I want to be an actor.

2
00:00:18,370 --> 00:00:19,500
P'Sun, do you want to try this?

3
00:00:19,870 --> 00:00:22,370
You don't have to call me P'. Just call me Sun.

4
00:00:22,600 --> 00:00:26,330
The only way you'll pass the audition is by sucking up to the higher-ups.

5
00:00:27,370 --> 00:00:28,500
But as for that Khajohn...

6
00:00:28,730 --> 00:00:30,400
If he doesn't have anyone’s  good in his hands,

7
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:32,470
then he probably won't last any longe herer in this company.

8
00:00:32,530 --> 00:00:35,530
Oh my god!

9
00:00:36,300 --> 00:00:38,200
If you're not ready to be an actor,

10
00:00:38,470 --> 00:00:39,570
I think it's better if you leave now.

11
00:00:39,870 --> 00:00:40,900
It's a waste of everyone’s time.

12
00:00:41,430 --> 00:00:42,300
I’m asking, who is it?

13
00:00:56,830 --> 00:00:59,370
Hey, do you think you're such a big shot around here?

14
00:00:59,830 --> 00:01:01,430
Bumping into me and not even apologizing?

15
00:01:02,400 --> 00:01:04,569
And still not apologizing? Dumbass!

16
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:06,930
Do you want to get beaten up?

17
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,230
Are you going to apologize to my bro?

18
00:01:13,330 --> 00:01:15,400
Fine. If you’re not doing anything,

19
00:01:15,770 --> 00:01:17,500
just consider this is your karma then.

20
00:01:18,700 --> 00:01:21,300
Just consider this is your karma then.

21
00:03:05,770 --> 00:03:06,330
Hello?

22
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:09,930
I have something I want to ask.

23
00:03:17,670 --> 00:03:18,470
Who the hell is he?

24
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:22,829
If you don't know, then go find out.

25
00:03:24,130 --> 00:03:25,200
Find a way to get rid of him.

26
00:03:26,770 --> 00:03:28,000
How you do it is your business.

27
00:03:29,870 --> 00:03:30,730
Just make sure he can't survive here.

28
00:03:38,130 --> 00:03:38,600
I’m hanging up now.

29
00:03:48,700 --> 00:03:49,270
Who's there?

30
00:03:57,370 --> 00:03:58,270
I’m asking, who is it?

31
00:04:21,899 --> 00:04:22,900
It's me.

32
00:04:27,530 --> 00:04:29,530
I thought that up here was supposed to be a quiet and peaceful place.

33
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:32,600
Why do I have to come across such a loud racket like this?

34
00:04:34,530 --> 00:04:35,130
I'm sorry.

35
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:38,170
I happened to hear a strange noise,

36
00:04:39,130 --> 00:04:40,730
So I thought someone was eavesdropping on my phone call.

37
00:04:42,030 --> 00:04:42,870
I didn't expect it to be...

38
00:04:43,300 --> 00:04:44,900
Is what you were talking about that important?

39
00:04:46,130 --> 00:04:47,430
To the point that you have to care for someone to eavesdrop?

40
00:04:53,630 --> 00:04:55,700
Or is it because it's about you wanting to get rid of the new kid?

41
00:05:00,170 --> 00:05:01,330
It's just a misunderstanding.

42
00:05:02,130 --> 00:05:03,770
I just want to do a little prank. That’s all.

43
00:05:05,570 --> 00:05:07,270
And I want to smoke a cigarette up here all alone.

44
00:05:14,170 --> 00:05:16,630
If I knew I'd run into you, I would have brought more cigarettes.

45
00:05:17,270 --> 00:05:19,070
Next time, may I join you up here for a smoke?

46
00:05:21,170 --> 00:05:22,830
Do you not understand the word "alone"?

47
00:05:25,970 --> 00:05:27,070
Are you going to leave anytime soon?

48
00:05:36,230 --> 00:05:36,430
Alright.

49
00:05:50,430 --> 00:05:52,370
You can come out now, Two-Baht Guy.

50
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:05,400
It’s him right? The one that you're planning to take revenge on?

51
00:06:09,970 --> 00:06:11,970
I’m asking you now if that ass kisser actor

52
00:06:12,630 --> 00:06:13,730
is the one you're planning to take revenge on.

53
00:06:16,370 --> 00:06:17,400
I’m not obligated to tell you.

54
00:06:24,570 --> 00:06:25,630
People are gossiping all over the building you know?

55
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,470
About you bringing a knife to the audition.

56
00:06:29,770 --> 00:06:32,130
Seriously, what were you thinking?

57
00:06:33,730 --> 00:06:35,770
That acting like that would make the judges like you?

58
00:06:39,130 --> 00:06:40,470
Passing the audition in one shot

59
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:43,030
doesn't mean you're skilled.

60
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,430
Or that you have any talent.

61
00:06:47,270 --> 00:06:49,300
If someone like you really wants to get revenge,

62
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:53,370
you need to rise to a much higher spot than he is.

63
00:06:56,430 --> 00:06:59,400
These days if you don’t have any backers you’re hopeless.

64
00:07:00,770 --> 00:07:02,200
You’ll never get there on your own.

65
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,400
Mind your own business.

66
00:07:06,730 --> 00:07:07,930
The reason you don't want me meddling in this

67
00:07:09,570 --> 00:07:10,900
is because you probably already have a backer in mind, right?

68
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:13,370
I don't know what you're talking about.

69
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:18,800
Is it Director Arthur?

70
00:07:21,970 --> 00:07:25,130
Director Arthur has people to track someone down?

71
00:07:26,570 --> 00:07:27,170
Who is that person?

72
00:07:27,830 --> 00:07:29,200
I don't know either, bro.

73
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:34,070
But I heard that the Director met this person like five years ago.

74
00:07:41,230 --> 00:07:42,870
Come to think of it, it's quite interesting.

75
00:07:43,870 --> 00:07:46,030
Becoming an actor just to get revenge.

76
00:07:48,200 --> 00:07:50,000
Anyway if you want me to help with anything

77
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:51,770
whenever it is

78
00:07:52,670 --> 00:07:54,300
what are you going to pay me back with?

79
00:08:00,770 --> 00:08:01,800
Think about that too just in case.

80
00:08:06,270 --> 00:08:06,500
Oh.

81
00:08:10,400 --> 00:08:12,030
And don't forget to pay for my cigarette.

82
00:08:48,370 --> 00:08:50,170
Anyways if you want me to help with anything

83
00:08:51,070 --> 00:08:51,870
whenever it is,

84
00:08:52,870 --> 00:08:54,500
what are you going to pay me back with?

85
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:58,000
Think about that too just in case.

86
00:08:59,970 --> 00:09:00,770
Damn it.

87
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:09,670
Dummy.

88
00:09:32,130 --> 00:09:34,830
Angie, eat carefully sweetie. It's hot.

89
00:09:38,430 --> 00:09:39,500
Now that you've passed the audition

90
00:09:39,530 --> 00:09:42,170
the next step is to take profile pictures

91
00:09:42,430 --> 00:09:44,700
to send to the artist management department so they can pitch you to clients.

92
00:09:45,570 --> 00:09:47,300
We need to make them look as good as possible.

93
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:49,970
You'll shoot with our photographer here at Dream.

94
00:09:51,100 --> 00:09:53,670
And Sun, you also need to update your resume and send it to HR.

95
00:09:57,770 --> 00:09:59,670
You don't happen to have a criminal record, right?

96
00:10:02,470 --> 00:10:04,470
I've been arrested and taken to the police station about 4 or 5 times.

97
00:10:16,070 --> 00:10:17,170
You two haven’t been arrested before?

98
00:10:27,570 --> 00:10:28,700
Have you?

99
00:10:37,770 --> 00:10:38,700
Sky, can I have that notebook?

100
00:10:39,030 --> 00:10:39,330
Here you go.

101
00:10:41,330 --> 00:10:42,630
Please watch Angie for a moment.

102
00:10:43,030 --> 00:10:43,570
Sure.

103
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:17,300
1. Dropped out of school.

104
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:20,730
2. No acting experience.

105
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:24,330
3. Doesn't use social media.

106
00:11:28,430 --> 00:11:29,500
4. Cannot speak English.

107
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:43,870
5. Has been arrested by the police.

108
00:11:53,300 --> 00:11:54,930
Angie have you ever played Rock-Paper-Scissors?

109
00:11:55,130 --> 00:11:55,830
Yes, I have.

110
00:11:55,870 --> 00:11:56,400
Wanna play with me?

111
00:11:56,900 --> 00:11:57,430
Okay.

112
00:11:57,470 --> 00:11:57,870
Okay.

113
00:11:58,770 --> 00:12:00,300
Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

114
00:12:00,730 --> 00:12:02,770
See? Love conquers all.

115
00:12:02,830 --> 00:12:04,930
What are you guys playing?

116
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:06,330
Rock-Paper-Scissors. Look!

117
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:08,030
That's so cheesy right? Sweetie.

118
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:09,400
It's not cheesy at all.

119
00:12:09,470 --> 00:12:09,870
Really?

120
00:12:10,730 --> 00:12:12,070
Move now.

121
00:12:13,870 --> 00:12:18,000
Do you know what the advantage of being an ordinary, unknown person is?

122
00:12:18,030 --> 00:12:21,030
It allows us to do whatever we want. Eat whatever we want, go wherever we want.

123
00:12:22,730 --> 00:12:23,600
Although you have to enjoy this feeling while it lasts.

124
00:12:24,430 --> 00:12:25,900
Because once you guys become famous

125
00:12:25,970 --> 00:12:27,570
you won't be able to just sit around here anymore.

126
00:12:30,970 --> 00:12:33,230
A toast to both of P'Khajohn's superstars.

127
00:12:34,370 --> 00:12:34,900
Cheers!

128
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:37,200
Cheers!

129
00:12:42,330 --> 00:12:43,170
Bottoms up.

130
00:13:16,670 --> 00:13:18,300
Hey, it's alright.

131
00:13:19,870 --> 00:13:22,230
I always knew someone like you would make it big one day.

132
00:13:23,970 --> 00:13:24,970
It's really totally fine.

133
00:13:27,270 --> 00:13:29,770
Because there's another path waiting for you, you little shit.

134
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:33,900
Go on.

135
00:13:37,700 --> 00:13:40,900
Although there's a lot of stuff left

136
00:13:41,530 --> 00:13:43,030
Can you help me deliver these first?

137
00:13:45,770 --> 00:13:46,570
Okay?

138
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:52,070
From this day forward,

139
00:13:52,770 --> 00:13:55,200
I will devote all the physical and mental strength I have

140
00:13:56,400 --> 00:14:00,100
solely to revenge.

141
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:30,000
Hello.

142
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:35,600
Hey, did you get a new haircut?

143
00:14:36,770 --> 00:14:37,570
Hello.

144
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:39,930
Oh, no, no, no. Not weird at all.

145
00:14:41,170 --> 00:14:44,000
I think it looks way better than your old, messy style.

146
00:14:47,670 --> 00:14:48,470
You really are

147
00:14:49,770 --> 00:14:52,230
a charming yet pitiful young man.

148
00:14:54,970 --> 00:14:55,770
Come on.

149
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:56,600
Ready?

150
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:59,070
The photographers should be waiting at the studio.

151
00:15:01,330 --> 00:15:02,130
Let's go.

152
00:15:07,870 --> 00:15:10,570
Whoa, bro, I thought I wouldn't make it in time.

153
00:15:11,370 --> 00:15:13,870
Didn't you have classes at the university this morning, Sky?

154
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,770
Yes, but the professor cancelled the morning class.

155
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:20,270
I knew Sun was having his profile photoshoot,

156
00:15:20,730 --> 00:15:21,770
so I came to keep him company.

157
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:25,930
Oh, please. Do you want to keep him company or just skip class?

158
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:29,700
Whatever. You have to go back to your faculty for the afternoon class anyway.

159
00:15:29,730 --> 00:15:30,200
Got it?

160
00:15:31,800 --> 00:15:32,570
I know.

161
00:15:33,270 --> 00:15:35,670
But for now, let me tag along with Sun first, okay?

162
00:15:36,470 --> 00:15:37,830
Please? Let me go too.

163
00:15:41,870 --> 00:15:43,030
Fine, fine, fine. Let's go.

164
00:15:45,230 --> 00:15:47,600
Oh, Sun, did you get a new haircut?

165
00:15:49,430 --> 00:15:51,200
That looks so sharp, man. Extremely sharp.

166
00:15:51,730 --> 00:15:52,330
Let's go.

167
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:56,000
What's so sharp?

168
00:16:03,670 --> 00:16:04,630
Hello.

169
00:16:04,930 --> 00:16:05,500
Hello.

170
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:09,330
Hi, I'm Khajohn. I brought my actor for the profile shoot.

171
00:16:09,530 --> 00:16:13,000
Oh, Mr. Khajohn. Actually, there are no photographers available today.

172
00:16:14,670 --> 00:16:15,870
What? What do you mean?

173
00:16:16,630 --> 00:16:19,270
Didn't I call to confirm the schedule yesterday?

174
00:16:20,070 --> 00:16:21,430
I'm not really sure either.

175
00:16:21,970 --> 00:16:23,630
They came in to work as usual this morning,

176
00:16:23,700 --> 00:16:25,800
but then suddenly packed up all their gear and left.

177
00:16:28,470 --> 00:16:29,430
I'll call them myself.

178
00:16:30,500 --> 00:16:31,130
Okay.

179
00:16:32,530 --> 00:16:34,200
Hello, I'm Khajohn.

180
00:16:34,970 --> 00:16:37,270
The one who mentioned yesterday that I'd bring an actor for a profile shoot.

181
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:43,470
What? All photographers were called to an outside event?

182
00:16:46,030 --> 00:16:48,830
Usually, events provide their own photographers, don't they?

183
00:16:52,100 --> 00:16:53,400
Okay, I get it.

184
00:16:54,430 --> 00:16:55,000
That's all.

185
00:16:58,170 --> 00:16:58,970
*Sigh*

186
00:17:00,330 --> 00:17:03,270
Can't we just go shoot somewhere else?

187
00:17:06,630 --> 00:17:07,829
Well, if we want to shoot elsewhere,

188
00:17:07,900 --> 00:17:10,900
we have to submit paperwork for approval from upper management first.

189
00:17:11,569 --> 00:17:12,599
Otherwise,

190
00:17:13,930 --> 00:17:15,170
we'd have to pay out of our own pockets.

191
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:19,369
And right now, I'm kind of broke.

192
00:17:23,970 --> 00:17:24,970
Come on, it's fine.

193
00:17:26,069 --> 00:17:28,670
It's okay if we don't shoot today. We still have plenty of time.

194
00:17:30,570 --> 00:17:32,070
Let's go to acting class with Teacher Phueng instead.

195
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:33,670
Right?

196
00:17:34,370 --> 00:17:35,200
Come on, let's go.

197
00:17:35,830 --> 00:17:36,170
Let's go.

198
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:36,770
Let's go!

199
00:17:37,700 --> 00:17:38,130
Sun.

200
00:17:40,030 --> 00:17:40,830
Teacher Phueng.

201
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:43,900
I can't let him join the class regardless.

202
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:45,930
I didn't receive any assignment for this.

203
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,700
But the contract clearly states

204
00:17:47,930 --> 00:17:50,070
that Sun can attend classes with you.

205
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:52,000
It's not that I don't want to teach him.

206
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:53,670
But this extra...

207
00:17:54,230 --> 00:17:54,970
Extra?

208
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:57,500
I mean the actor himself

209
00:17:57,970 --> 00:18:00,130
hasn't even signed a contract with the company yet.

210
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:06,000
He's still just a trainee, isn't he?

211
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:11,800
I really want to help but I also have to follow company policy.

212
00:18:13,970 --> 00:18:15,130
Please try to understand me too.

213
00:18:17,300 --> 00:18:19,900
Please check this evening's schedule to see if there are other classes.

214
00:18:20,270 --> 00:18:22,470
And update everyone via email, please.

215
00:18:22,870 --> 00:18:25,830
Look, I don't know why you suddenly won't accept any new kid,

216
00:18:27,330 --> 00:18:28,830
even though it was perfectly fine before.

217
00:18:29,370 --> 00:18:31,070
Sky even used to study with you.

218
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:35,100
Excuse me, teacher.

219
00:18:35,830 --> 00:18:37,970
You aren't intentionally neglecting your duties, are you?

220
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:41,530
Are you accusing me of being too lazy to teach?

221
00:18:42,930 --> 00:18:44,930
That is now crossing the line, Manager.

222
00:18:55,570 --> 00:18:56,800
These days if you don’t have any backers you’re hopeless.

223
00:18:57,870 --> 00:19:00,930
You’ll never get there on your own.

224
00:19:05,330 --> 00:19:06,500
I have nothing left to say.

225
00:19:07,170 --> 00:19:07,970
I'll take my leave.

226
00:19:08,300 --> 00:19:09,100
Go ahead.

227
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:23,470
Damn it!

228
00:19:24,770 --> 00:19:25,570
I'm sorry.

229
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:33,600
I'm really sorry about that.

230
00:19:34,830 --> 00:19:37,000
Everything seems so difficult because of me.

231
00:19:38,230 --> 00:19:39,630
It's because of P'Sunny, actually.

232
00:19:39,900 --> 00:19:41,600
It's very obvious that he’s targeting you.

233
00:19:50,830 --> 00:19:52,400
Let me think about what we should do next.

234
00:19:57,970 --> 00:19:59,370
I need to use the toilet.

235
00:20:35,170 --> 00:20:35,970
Hello?

236
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:38,300
What's up?

237
00:20:39,470 --> 00:20:40,530
Ready to have a backer now?

238
00:20:45,030 --> 00:20:46,430
You said you could help me.

239
00:20:47,970 --> 00:20:50,700
That's why you told me to go think about it.

240
00:20:52,230 --> 00:20:53,570
And have you made up your mind?

241
00:20:55,930 --> 00:20:59,070
Too bad I have nothing to offer you.

242
00:21:00,930 --> 00:21:02,730
So I didn't know what to give you.

243
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:08,230
I will give you myself.

244
00:21:08,430 --> 00:21:11,470
Therefore, you must pay a deposit first.

245
00:21:11,970 --> 00:21:15,530
The question is, if I have you,

246
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:17,500
how do I benefit?

247
00:21:18,570 --> 00:21:20,970
I can probably surprise you from time to time.

248
00:21:22,570 --> 00:21:23,930
So, what is it that you want?

249
00:21:44,330 --> 00:21:45,430
P'Khajohn.

250
00:21:50,930 --> 00:21:53,670
Who is the best photographer in this industry?

251
00:21:56,200 --> 00:22:01,400
Well if we're talking about the number one, it would probably be Phakin.

252
00:22:03,930 --> 00:22:04,900
Why do you ask?

253
00:22:07,200 --> 00:22:08,500
I want him to take my pictures.

254
00:22:17,430 --> 00:22:19,200
Are you out of your mind?

255
00:22:20,100 --> 00:22:21,800
Like he'd ever do that for a nobody like you.

256
00:22:21,970 --> 00:22:24,830
His work is top-tier, he's incredibly famous.

257
00:22:25,700 --> 00:22:29,030
And besides, he's the type who won't just shoot anyone unless they really catch his eye.

258
00:22:30,300 --> 00:22:32,830
Anyways he's that good, but...

259
00:22:32,900 --> 00:22:35,370
Forget about him. He's incredibly hard as hell to work with.

260
00:22:40,730 --> 00:22:41,900
We are going to see him now.

261
00:22:45,870 --> 00:22:48,000
How? Who contacted him? Who's paying?

262
00:22:49,900 --> 00:22:51,100
Someone has already arranged it.

263
00:22:57,100 --> 00:22:58,070
Don't tell me that

264
00:22:59,670 --> 00:23:02,600
you’re getting yourself involved with some backer or some shady investor.

265
00:23:02,770 --> 00:23:04,200
- He’s no…
- If so then you shouldn’t.

266
00:23:05,130 --> 00:23:07,570
I'm telling you right now that you need to back off.

267
00:23:08,870 --> 00:23:10,070
It's not worth the risk.

268
00:23:13,130 --> 00:23:14,130
He isn't an investor.

269
00:23:16,670 --> 00:23:18,370
And right now, I don't exactly know who he really is either.

270
00:23:23,070 --> 00:23:24,400
Let's hurry up.

271
00:23:25,170 --> 00:23:26,230
Hey, wait!

272
00:23:26,770 --> 00:23:27,400
Sun!

273
00:23:28,430 --> 00:23:29,270
Hey!

274
00:23:47,700 --> 00:23:50,070
Please come this way and wait for a moment.

275
00:23:50,470 --> 00:23:51,130
Thank you.

276
00:23:51,170 --> 00:23:51,470
You’re welcome.

277
00:24:00,930 --> 00:24:03,570
This place is insanely gorgeous.

278
00:24:08,370 --> 00:24:09,170
Wow.

279
00:24:18,570 --> 00:24:20,070
Mr. Phakin.

280
00:24:23,300 --> 00:24:26,130
Mr. Phakin.

281
00:24:26,470 --> 00:24:27,730
Who are you guys?

282
00:24:31,430 --> 00:24:34,830
Uh, I'm Khajohn. I'm...

283
00:24:36,500 --> 00:24:37,700
And what are you doing in my house?

284
00:24:38,400 --> 00:24:42,770
I brought Sun here for a profile photoshoot with you.

285
00:24:52,830 --> 00:24:53,630
I'm not doing it.

286
00:24:56,870 --> 00:24:59,270
What do you think this place is? Huh?

287
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:01,200
You think you can just show up whenever you want?

288
00:25:02,130 --> 00:25:05,130
Next time, if you want to come, you must make an appointment first.

289
00:25:11,530 --> 00:25:13,300
With or without appointment. Does it make any difference?

290
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:17,400
Because you only choose to shoot people you like anyway.

291
00:25:32,070 --> 00:25:33,570
You're starting to interest me.

292
00:25:39,270 --> 00:25:40,870
Why don't you try...

293
00:25:43,470 --> 00:25:44,830
taking off your shirt for me to see?

294
00:26:13,070 --> 00:26:14,200
Uh, wait, wait, wait, wait.

295
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:16,970
Only take off what Mr. Phakin has asked you to.

296
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:03,530
Have you ever worked as a laborer before?

297
00:27:04,930 --> 00:27:08,200
Your muscles don't look like they're from working out.

298
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:12,970
Oh, Sun has worked many different jobs.

299
00:27:15,330 --> 00:27:16,830
I do any job that pays.

300
00:27:20,670 --> 00:27:22,070
Sounds unusual.

301
00:27:23,970 --> 00:27:25,370
But with a face like this,

302
00:27:26,700 --> 00:27:28,100
you look pretty ordinary.

303
00:27:30,230 --> 00:27:31,330
Seriously, let me ask you.

304
00:27:34,100 --> 00:27:36,830
How can you be so confident you'll survive in this industry?

305
00:27:39,630 --> 00:27:40,930
So, are you going to take my pictures or not?

306
00:27:43,930 --> 00:27:44,900
If not,

307
00:27:45,930 --> 00:27:48,130
I can go find a better photographer.

308
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:06,800
I'll do it.

309
00:28:09,400 --> 00:28:12,170
But you have to be my nude model in return.

310
00:28:15,870 --> 00:28:16,970
Can you do that?

311
00:28:20,230 --> 00:28:21,030
Deal.

312
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:23,400
Deal.

313
00:28:43,870 --> 00:28:45,970
Are you really sure about shooting nude for Mr. Phakin?

314
00:28:47,170 --> 00:28:48,730
Do you even know what that means?

315
00:28:50,730 --> 00:28:51,530
I know.

316
00:28:52,630 --> 00:28:55,430
Then you must know how it'll affect your future.

317
00:28:56,170 --> 00:28:58,000
Can't you call that person to

318
00:28:58,030 --> 00:29:00,270
help you with just the profile, so you don't have to do the nude photoshoot?

319
00:29:00,830 --> 00:29:02,230
I didn't ask him to help with that.

320
00:29:05,800 --> 00:29:06,630
What do you mean?

321
00:29:08,170 --> 00:29:10,470
Then how did you manage to persuade me to bring you here?

322
00:29:13,630 --> 00:29:15,530
I just believed in your words.

323
00:29:16,930 --> 00:29:18,070
My words?

324
00:29:18,970 --> 00:29:21,570
You said I have what it takes to go far.

325
00:29:23,300 --> 00:29:24,100
So I thought that

326
00:29:24,900 --> 00:29:27,170
Mr. Phakin would definitely want to take my pictures.

327
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:34,900
Thank you, Manager.

328
00:29:51,030 --> 00:29:53,300
But if you didn't ask him to help with this,

329
00:29:54,000 --> 00:29:55,170
then what did you ask him to help with?

330
00:30:12,770 --> 00:30:15,700
P'Na, how is it? Is everything ready?

331
00:30:15,730 --> 00:30:17,430
Got it. Okay.

332
00:30:19,500 --> 00:30:20,370
Lighting is okay.

333
00:30:39,930 --> 00:30:41,800
I think I remember you.

334
00:30:42,930 --> 00:30:45,670
Your name is Sawai?

335
00:30:48,700 --> 00:30:49,500
Sa...

336
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:51,800
Sabai?

337
00:30:52,700 --> 00:30:53,570
Smile?

338
00:30:57,030 --> 00:30:58,200
My name is Sky.

339
00:31:00,470 --> 00:31:03,030
Sky. Sky, it is.

340
00:31:04,130 --> 00:31:06,100
Come pose for me for a bit.

341
00:31:08,770 --> 00:31:09,870
I need to test the lighting.

342
00:31:14,670 --> 00:31:20,530
Why? Or do you not want me to take photos with the people your manager brought along that badly?

343
00:31:21,570 --> 00:31:23,300
Try turning to look at the camera.

344
00:31:27,530 --> 00:31:28,330
No, it's not that.

345
00:31:29,900 --> 00:31:31,270
Don't forget to take off your shoes.

346
00:31:37,600 --> 00:31:40,430
Okay, let me check the light exposure first.

347
00:31:59,830 --> 00:32:02,830
Move the key light to the left and lower it by one-third.

348
00:32:02,870 --> 00:32:07,100
And move the negative fill slightly closer to the model.

349
00:32:07,300 --> 00:32:07,870
Got it.

350
00:32:13,130 --> 00:32:14,500
Turn sideways a bit.

351
00:32:15,570 --> 00:32:16,400
Either side is fine.

352
00:32:20,600 --> 00:32:22,430
Try turning to look at the camera.

353
00:32:40,930 --> 00:32:41,770
That's enough.

354
00:32:43,630 --> 00:32:44,930
Excuse me, I need to go to the restroom.

355
00:32:45,730 --> 00:32:46,930
What is wrong with you?

356
00:32:53,270 --> 00:32:54,070
Where are you going?

357
00:32:54,370 --> 00:32:55,170
To the restroom.

358
00:32:56,230 --> 00:32:56,830
Sun, hurry up.

359
00:33:04,870 --> 00:33:05,670
Ready?

360
00:33:08,830 --> 00:33:09,630
Wait.

361
00:33:11,470 --> 00:33:12,730
Don't forget to wipe your feet before going in.

362
00:33:28,030 --> 00:33:29,230
Look at the camera.

363
00:33:32,170 --> 00:33:32,970
Ready?

364
00:33:37,430 --> 00:33:38,800
Tilt your head down a bit.

365
00:33:42,330 --> 00:33:43,170
Your eyes are too stiff.

366
00:33:52,330 --> 00:33:53,370
That's not it.

367
00:33:56,600 --> 00:33:57,400
Ugh, seriously?

368
00:33:59,430 --> 00:34:01,530
You really have never modeled before, have you?

369
00:34:07,400 --> 00:34:09,500
Your posture looks unnatural.

370
00:34:12,570 --> 00:34:16,230
And your gaze looks emotionless.

371
00:34:19,570 --> 00:34:21,370
How can someone like this be an actor?

372
00:34:25,030 --> 00:34:27,100
But you do have one advantageous quality.

373
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:29,630
You aren't camera-shy.

374
00:34:31,969 --> 00:34:35,170
Usually, you aren't really afraid of anything, right?

375
00:34:39,230 --> 00:34:40,670
I've been afraid long enough.

376
00:34:46,770 --> 00:34:49,670
Have you ever had a lover then?

377
00:34:50,830 --> 00:34:55,100
Parents, siblings, or anyone?

378
00:34:57,070 --> 00:34:57,870
No one

379
00:34:58,970 --> 00:35:00,100
No one?

380
00:35:03,430 --> 00:35:05,430
You must have experienced losses before.

381
00:35:11,130 --> 00:35:13,730
Then try to think of what you've lost.

382
00:35:15,330 --> 00:35:17,300
Think of what you want to go back and fix,

383
00:35:18,670 --> 00:35:22,430
but you no longer have the chance to do so.

384
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:37,300
Exactly like this.

385
00:35:43,530 --> 00:35:44,670
Look into the camera.

386
00:35:46,300 --> 00:35:47,900
Your losses…

387
00:35:55,530 --> 00:35:57,370
You can’t turn back time.

388
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:30,530
Thank you for your help, Mr. Phakin.

389
00:36:34,270 --> 00:36:36,230
Don't forget what you said either.

390
00:36:38,300 --> 00:36:39,370
Whenever I'm free,

391
00:36:41,500 --> 00:36:42,500
I'll let you know.

392
00:36:53,700 --> 00:36:55,730
I can't believe we got this lucky.

393
00:36:55,930 --> 00:36:57,100
You're amazing, Sun!

394
00:36:57,300 --> 00:36:59,100
Mr. Phakin actually agreed to shoot for you.

395
00:37:00,500 --> 00:37:03,100
You really are something else.

396
00:37:03,730 --> 00:37:04,830
Even before getting famous,

397
00:37:05,030 --> 00:37:07,630
you got a top photographer like Mr. Phakin to do your profile.

398
00:37:09,300 --> 00:37:10,100
Incredible!

399
00:37:15,030 --> 00:37:18,070
Hello, Boss. Guess where I am right now.

400
00:37:18,300 --> 00:37:21,100
Oh, I don't care where you are.

401
00:37:21,270 --> 00:37:23,400
I only care about what you've done.

402
00:37:23,500 --> 00:37:24,930
Teacher Phueng came to complain to me

403
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:27,130
that you went on a ranting spree at her

404
00:37:27,230 --> 00:37:30,070
about her not letting your trainee join the acting class.

405
00:37:30,500 --> 00:37:31,230
Uh, wait a minute.

406
00:37:31,670 --> 00:37:34,270
Teacher Phueng accused me of going on a ranting spree at her like that?

407
00:37:34,530 --> 00:37:35,830
Exactly.

408
00:37:36,200 --> 00:37:39,100
Do you know that doing this could get your salary docked?

409
00:37:39,470 --> 00:37:40,500
Salary docked?

410
00:37:41,770 --> 00:37:42,630
Wait a minute, Boss.

411
00:37:43,330 --> 00:37:44,800
As an artist manager,

412
00:37:44,830 --> 00:37:47,330
don't I have the right to protect what we are entitled to from the company?

413
00:37:49,700 --> 00:37:51,870
Boss, don't just listen to one side. Please listen to my side too.

414
00:37:53,300 --> 00:37:58,000
I don't care about your reasons. Because right now, the complaint has already reached upper management.

415
00:37:58,670 --> 00:38:00,030
Anyway, when you're free,

416
00:38:00,170 --> 00:38:02,500
come over to receive the complaint notice at the office.

417
00:38:04,370 --> 00:38:06,230
Boss, don't leave just yet. I'm heading back to the office now.

418
00:38:10,130 --> 00:38:11,130
What did Teacher Phueng do?

419
00:38:11,670 --> 00:38:12,930
Filed a complaint with upper management.

420
00:38:14,900 --> 00:38:16,500
Regarding me bringing Sun to the acting class.

421
00:38:16,570 --> 00:38:18,900
Suddenly she accused me of shouting non-stop at her.

422
00:38:21,830 --> 00:38:23,500
We can't just stay on the defensive about this.

423
00:38:24,670 --> 00:38:26,030
Go back to class first, we'll split up here.

424
00:38:26,870 --> 00:38:29,030
As for you, come back to the office with me.

425
00:38:35,430 --> 00:38:36,570
Please look after P'Khajohn.

426
00:38:39,230 --> 00:38:40,470
Khajohn won't tolerate this anymore.

427
00:38:43,930 --> 00:38:47,200
Boss, listen to what happened from my side first.

428
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:51,200
Today I booked the office photographer for a profile shoot,

429
00:38:51,530 --> 00:38:54,170
but they were suddenly called to Sunny's event out of nowhere.

430
00:38:55,730 --> 00:38:57,530
And when I tried to take Sun to acting class,

431
00:38:57,930 --> 00:39:01,870
Teacher Phueng out of nowhere refused, even though the contract clearly states he can attend.

432
00:39:04,300 --> 00:39:09,300
Boss, do you understand what's really going on now?

433
00:39:10,700 --> 00:39:13,100
It's not that I don't understand.

434
00:39:13,800 --> 00:39:16,770
But right now, the complaint has already reached upper management.

435
00:39:17,930 --> 00:39:23,000
And if you want to find an excuse or defense for yourself, then go find clear evidence.

436
00:39:23,300 --> 00:39:25,500
If you’re just throwing words out there, nobody will believe you.

437
00:39:30,970 --> 00:39:31,770
Just a moment, please.

438
00:39:42,930 --> 00:39:48,570
Hello? How does it feel? I heard your new kid didn't get to shoot his profile.

439
00:39:49,500 --> 00:39:50,830
Plus you got a complaint from Teacher Phueng as well.

440
00:39:51,870 --> 00:39:54,070
This is why you shouldn’t be doing something pointlessly stupid.

441
00:39:57,700 --> 00:40:01,070
Oh, it's good that you called. I actually have something to thank you for.

442
00:40:02,970 --> 00:40:04,870
Thank me? Thank me for what?

443
00:40:05,770 --> 00:40:08,370
Well, if you hadn't called away all the photographers,

444
00:40:08,970 --> 00:40:12,670
my kid wouldn't have gotten a top photographer like Mr. Phakin to do his profile.

445
00:40:14,700 --> 00:40:15,500
Mr. Phakin?

446
00:40:17,730 --> 00:40:18,470
Listen up, Khajohn.

447
00:40:18,800 --> 00:40:21,430
If you're going to brag, keep it within reality.

448
00:40:22,200 --> 00:40:25,430
You? As if you could really work with him.

449
00:40:25,730 --> 00:40:26,530
Are you insane?

450
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:30,400
Just wait and see his Instagram in the next two or three days.

451
00:40:31,430 --> 00:40:33,670
Mr. Phakin will probably post the photos he took today.

452
00:40:35,470 --> 00:40:36,070
Oh,

453
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:38,370
as for the matter with Teacher Phueng, I must thank you too.

454
00:40:39,630 --> 00:40:42,470
Since Kru Phueng said she won't accept any more trainees,

455
00:40:43,370 --> 00:40:45,430
the Boss has already approved the order

456
00:40:46,330 --> 00:40:48,900
to arrange a special private acting coach for us.

457
00:40:51,430 --> 00:40:52,800
It won't be hard for me to find out

458
00:40:52,970 --> 00:40:54,430
which coach you ended up getting.

459
00:40:55,370 --> 00:41:00,870
Let me tell, you that whoever has you as a manager won’t survive in this industry.

460
00:41:06,870 --> 00:41:09,870
What are you talking about? What kind of nonsense is this?

461
00:41:10,530 --> 00:41:11,800
I haven't approved anything yet,

462
00:41:12,030 --> 00:41:14,900
about letting you find a private acting coach for your kid.

463
00:41:15,730 --> 00:41:18,630
Come on, Boss. Just wait and see.

464
00:41:19,100 --> 00:41:23,330
Soon enough, someone will file a complaint to cancel your order anyway.

465
00:41:26,770 --> 00:41:27,570
Boss.

466
00:41:29,570 --> 00:41:32,530
It couldn't be any clearer that my kid is being bullied.

467
00:41:34,730 --> 00:41:35,870
I understand.

468
00:41:36,270 --> 00:41:43,200
But still, the lie about getting a photographer like Mr. Phakin to take his pictures is still outrageous.

469
00:41:43,530 --> 00:41:46,230
If you're going to brag, can you keep it reasonable?

470
00:41:46,930 --> 00:41:48,870
I'm not bragging, I'm speaking the truth.

471
00:41:49,270 --> 00:41:51,300
I just got back from Mr. Phakin's studio.

472
00:41:52,530 --> 00:41:55,230
Do you know that the moment Mr. Phakin saw my kid,

473
00:41:55,730 --> 00:41:57,830
he liked him instantly and promised to take his pictures.

474
00:42:00,270 --> 00:42:02,100
I took some behind-the-scenes footage for you to see

475
00:42:03,370 --> 00:42:04,530
as proof too.

476
00:42:12,570 --> 00:42:13,370
Whoa.

477
00:42:18,200 --> 00:42:21,370
Did Mr. Phakin really take his pictures?

478
00:42:31,730 --> 00:42:34,600
Anyway, if someone calls regarding Sun's acting class.

479
00:42:37,700 --> 00:42:42,230
Could you please approve for Sun to study along with the other kids in class.

480
00:42:50,900 --> 00:42:54,630
Oh. Before coming in earlier, you had something to ask him, right?

481
00:42:56,770 --> 00:42:57,570
What do you want to know?

482
00:43:00,530 --> 00:43:01,830
So, what is it that you want?

483
00:43:03,800 --> 00:43:04,730
How big are you in here?

484
00:43:07,730 --> 00:43:08,870
Bigger than you think, perhaps.

485
00:43:09,970 --> 00:43:13,200
Then could you have an employee called in to be scolded?

486
00:43:14,100 --> 00:43:14,900
Who?

487
00:43:15,170 --> 00:43:16,270
My own manager.

488
00:43:17,530 --> 00:43:22,170
I want to know who ordered P'Khajohn to be called in and scolded.

489
00:43:26,530 --> 00:43:27,700
Can't you tell me?

490
00:43:30,630 --> 00:43:34,230
No, I just didn't expect anyone to actually ask this question.

491
00:43:37,770 --> 00:43:40,430
Actually, I received the order from someone else too.

492
00:43:41,070 --> 00:43:42,730
That person only said

493
00:43:43,030 --> 00:43:48,270
if anyone asks, tell them, "Am I big enough, Mr. Two-Baht?"

494
00:43:58,770 --> 00:43:59,570
Something along those lines.

495
00:44:18,470 --> 00:44:20,100
Come to this location now.

496
00:44:47,630 --> 00:44:48,400
Wait a moment, sir.

497
00:44:51,230 --> 00:44:53,570
This club is for members only.

498
00:44:54,070 --> 00:44:56,200
Non-members are not allowed to enter.

499
00:44:57,270 --> 00:44:59,400
Or you can provide the name of the person you came with.

500
00:44:59,800 --> 00:45:02,070
We will check today's guest list for you.

501
00:45:05,370 --> 00:45:06,170
Uh...

502
00:45:07,670 --> 00:45:08,430
Who did you come with, sir?

503
00:45:11,300 --> 00:45:12,100
Hello.

504
00:45:13,070 --> 00:45:14,130
You are Two-Baht, right?

505
00:45:15,600 --> 00:45:16,400
Two-Baht?

506
00:45:17,100 --> 00:45:18,730
It's an alias used by the client.

507
00:45:19,100 --> 00:45:20,230
I'll take over from here.

508
00:45:20,730 --> 00:45:21,270
Okay, sir.

509
00:45:21,300 --> 00:45:22,100
Please go ahead.

510
00:45:22,330 --> 00:45:23,230
Please come this way, Mr. Two-Baht.

511
00:45:23,800 --> 00:45:24,800
Please come this way, Mr. Two-Baht.

512
00:45:35,930 --> 00:45:37,100
Please, this way.

513
00:46:05,600 --> 00:46:06,630
Follow me, please.

514
00:46:24,000 --> 00:46:25,570
He is waiting for you in there.

515
00:46:29,030 --> 00:46:29,830
Please.

516
00:46:48,870 --> 00:46:49,670
Have a seat.

517
00:47:11,930 --> 00:47:13,070
Who are you really?

518
00:47:16,970 --> 00:47:17,570
A partner.

519
00:47:18,770 --> 00:47:21,670
To be exact, one of the partners.

520
00:47:24,930 --> 00:47:28,070
Meaning a partner of this place?

521
00:47:32,070 --> 00:47:33,000
And what is your name?

522
00:47:34,470 --> 00:47:35,270
What about yours?

523
00:47:36,800 --> 00:47:38,130
Before asking for someone else's name,

524
00:47:39,170 --> 00:47:40,900
why don’t you tell me your own first?

525
00:47:42,530 --> 00:47:44,130
Or do you prefer the name "Mr. Two-Baht"?

526
00:47:50,730 --> 00:47:51,530
Sun.

527
00:47:56,400 --> 00:47:56,870
Jay.

528
00:48:16,330 --> 00:48:17,530
Remember what I once told you?

529
00:48:18,570 --> 00:48:21,600
Nothing in this world comes for free.

530
00:48:24,530 --> 00:48:28,800
Now, the fee for having me scold your manager has increased by another fifty thousand.

531
00:48:29,830 --> 00:48:31,100
The cigarette fee is two hundred thousand.

532
